		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Heather Kirn Lanier</span></strong> is the author of <em>Teaching in the Terrordome: Two Years in West Baltimore with Teach for America</em> and the poetry chapbook <em>The Story You Tell Yourself</em>. After a decade of moving &mdash; from Maryland to Japan to Ohio to California and back to Ohio again &mdash; she and her family have settled in Bennington, Vermont, where they live among unpacked boxes. She blogs about her special-needs daughter at <a href="https://starinhereye.wordpress.com">starinhereye.wordpress.com</a>.</p><a href="/contributors/heather-kirn-lanier" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
